Paper: hep-th/0003019

Date: 2000-03-02

Title: Lectures on Strings, D-branes and Gauge Theories

Authors: Hugo Garcia-Compean, Oscar Loaiza-Brito

Comments: 37+1 pages, LaTeX file, no figures

In these lectures we review the basic ideas of perturbative andnon-perturbative string theory. On the non-perturbative side we give anintroduction to D-branes and string duality. The elementary concepts of non-BPSbranes and noncommutative gauge theories are also discussed.